    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. The CNN surrogate achieves MAE=0.031 RH units and R²=0.961 on held-out CFD data, and predictions agree with experimental hemolysis measurements within 7.8% at all 5 COU operating points. Reproducibility of CNN training was reviewed informally and judged adequate by the engineering team. The 6 non-assessed factors are acceptable per MRL 2 scoping. The model is accepted for use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device under the defined COU.",
